description.narrative: Girls and boys and their mothers living in humanitarian conditions have access to life saving health interventions from pregnancy to adolescence., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Adolescent girls and boys, mothers and fathers, and community leaders in 106 districts adopt 11 key life-saving, care and protective behaviours for children and women
